My meme

I made this meme on how I feel learning the different coding languages 

library(magick)
# importing the cat pics
confused_cat <- image_read("https://i.redd.it/7k24xova0ya11.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(200)

happy_cat <- image_read("https://i.imgflip.com/cnudu.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(200)
# making the text and the reaction box
java_text <- image_blank(width = 200, 
                         height = 200, 
                         color = "#000000") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Learning\nJava",
                 color = "#FFFFFF",
                 size = 40,
                 font = "Helvetica",
                 gravity = "center")


python_text <- image_blank(width = 200, 
                           height = 200, 
                           color = "#000000") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Learning\nPython",
                 color = "#FFFFFF",
                 size = 40,
                 font = "Helvetica",
                 gravity = "center")
# adding the pic of the cats and the text
first_row <- c(confused_cat, java_text) %>%
  image_append()


second_row <- c(happy_cat, python_text) %>%
  image_append()
# joining the two cat and texts together
meme <- c(first_row, second_row) %>%
  image_append(stack = TRUE)
meme

meme %>% image_write("my_meme.png")

My animation gif

I made this gif on funny cats and how how there reactions protary my reaction to uni 

#importing the pics of cats to be used as frames
sad_cat <- image_read("https://wompampsupport.azureedge.net/fetchimage?siteId=7575&v=2&jpgQuality=100&width=700&url=https%3A%2F%2Fi.kym-cdn.com%2Fphotos%2Fimages%2Fnewsfeed%2F001%2F878%2F329%2Fdfa.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(200)
mild_cat <- image_read("https://www.idlememe.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/polite-cat-meme-idlememe-1.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(200)
happy_cat <- image_read("https://i.imgflip.com/cnudu.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(200)
cool_cat <- image_read("https://www.meme-arsenal.com/memes/4bf4932055a81bc2c536a20e8f5ac693.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(200)


# creating each frame, with a given text
frame1 <- sad_cat %>%
  image_annotate(text = 'Going to uni', size = 20, gravity = "center")

frame2 <- mild_cat %>%
  image_annotate(text = 'Done most of\nyour work', size = 20, gravity = "center")

frame3 <- happy_cat %>%
  image_annotate(text = 'Knowing you\nhave stats', size = 20, gravity = "center")

frame4 <- cool_cat %>%
  image_annotate(text = 'Realsing you\ncan just look at cats', size = 20, gravity = "center")



# putting the frames in order using a vector
frames <- c(frame1, frame2, frame3, frame4)

# creating an animation
animation <- image_morph(frames) %>%
  image_animate(fps = 4)
animation

animation %>% 
  image_write("my_animation.gif")
